miscConds.notes: Defendant must pay all outstanding fees and court obligations including costs of supervision during the term of probation.   If supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.

No alcohol or controlled substances except by prescription. Random UA's are authorized. Must obtain and maintain full time verifiable employment. Must continue with psychological counseling and any other counseling deemed appropriate by agent. No violent contact with the victim.  Defendant is to reside with her mother in her mother's home rather than anywhere else. Defendant must obey all rules and regulations while on probation.
